reviews.review_text:
Studio Quality Sound The mix is hot hot hot -- accurate without losing anything to distortion on the key element, the bass guitar. The whole show is immaculate. All instruments are equipresent.. Vocals right in the pocket. Total clarity and balance. How could anyone get such a live recording in 1971?

Never heard this night before but it's another of those proverbial all-time keepers. All songs are played very well. I long for the days when there weren't setlists and there were long between song tune-ups.  It helped you to appreciate what was going down.

It was 1971 and very few of us were in a hurry. No one worried about anything.

It does a heart good when searching around and it latches on to one of these.
